name: Consistent Care Services- COVID Vaccine Site
address: 1235 North Post St. Suite 201, Spokane WA, 99205
vaccines: Janssen COVID-19 Vaccine, Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine, Pfizer-BioNTech COVID-19 Vaccine
info:
******All patients at this clinic will receive a $50 Visa gift card that can be used anywhere Visa is accepted.*** You will need to sign a consent form at the clinic verifying you received the gift card.  This is a clinic for 1st or 2nd doses of the Pfizer or Moderna COVID-19 vaccine or the single dose of the Johnson & Johnson*** All patients 12 years old and older can register for the Pfizer vaccine only. (If 12-17 years old for the Pfizer vaccine, you must be with a parent or guardian or have parental/guardian consent) Vaccinations at the Consistent Care Services COVID Vaccine Clinic are by appointment only. The clinic is located at 1235 N. Post St., Spokane WA 99201. The clinic is located upstairs in suite 201. There is elevator access or stairs. 
***Residents of ANY state are now eligible for the vaccine, but you still must have photo ID***
***Parking is free on the West side of the building only in stalls 14-55. Please do not come to your appointment if you are sick*** 
***Please no outside food or drinks***  
*VERY IMPORTANT*
***Please complete all the insurance/Medicare/Medicaid information when registering online for your appointment to avoid filling it out at the clinic***
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Thurston County Public Health Medical Reserve Corp
address: Capital Mall - 625 Black Lake Blvd SW, Olympia WA, 98502
info: This is a Johnson & Johnson mobile clinic being held at Capital Mall, 625 Black Lake Blvd SW, Olympia WA, 98502 for anyone age 18 and older from 12pm-8pm.  We will be located inside the mall, closest to the Sephora end of the mall and next to the Buckle store. Please bring a form of identification with you to your appointment - ID card, passport, or other document with your name and birthday on it. • Wear a short-sleeved shirt, but dress with layers, if needed. • Please arrive at your scheduled appointment time. • Waiting at least 15 minutes after vaccination is required.
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Olympic Pharmacy and Healthcare Services - COVID Vaccine Venue
address: 4700 Pt Fosdick Dr, Suite 120, Gig Harbor Washington, 98335
info:
**THIS CLINIC IS FOR JANSSEN (JOHNSON&JOHNSON) VACCINATION ONLY**

You must be 18 years of age or older.
Please bring your State ID, and if you have insurance, please bring your insurance card or Medicare B card (red,white and blue card).
Please do not come to the clinic if you are not feeling well.
Please wear loose sleeved, short sleeved or sleeveless shirt
When you enter Olympic Pharmacy, please follow COVID clinic signs to the back conference/fitting area. This clinic is not in the pharmacy area.
Please arrive as close as possible to your scheduled time to prevent crowding that will impede appropriate social distancing.
Please be prepared to wait 15-30 minutes after vaccination for observation of adverse reactions.
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.
